Ginger Beef and Ramen Noodle Soup
  --Cook's Country

1 lb flank steak, trimmed
1 tsp vegetable oil
8 c low sodium chicken broth
2" piece ginger, halved lengthwise and smashed
2 1/2" strips lime zest + 1 tbsp juice
4 packages instant ramen noodles (discard seasoning packets)
5 scallions, sliced thin
1/4 c shoyu
1/4 fresh cilantro leaves

Pat steak dry with paper towels and season with salt and pepper. Heat oil in 12" skillet over medium high heat until just smoking. Add steak and cook until well browned and tep registers 125F for medium rare, 6-8 min, flipping once. Transfer to cutting board, tent loosely with foil, and let rest for 5 min. Slice steak in half lengthwise, then slice thin against grain. Meanwhile, bring both, ginger, and lime zest to boil in dutch oven over medium high heat. Reduce heat to medium low, cover, and simmer for 10 min. Remove ginger and zest. Add noodles and cook until tender, ~3 min. Stir in scallions, shoyu, and lime juice. Ladle noodles and broth into 4 bowls, nad divide steak and cilantro evenly among bowls. Serve.

Note: try with other noodles, not instant ramen
